                "title": "Micropilot: Automation of fluorescence microscopy-based imaging for systems biology", 
                "abstract": "Quantitative microscopy relies on imaging of large cell numbers but is often hampered by time-consuming manual selection of specific cells. The 'Micropilot' software automatically detects cells of interest and launches complex imaging experiments including three-dimensional multicolor time-lapse or fluorescence recovery after photobleaching in live cells. In three independent experimental setups this allowed us to statistically analyze biological processes in detail and is thus a powerful tool for systems biology. Â© 2011 Nature America, Inc. All rights reserved.", 
